It advances ML by formalizing **"democratic alignment"**—embedding collective reasoning and procedural justice via social choice theory and participatory ML architectures. The goal is to enable stakeholder co-ownership of AI in public decision-making through sustained, language-mediated feedback, moving beyond tokenistic ethics to institutionalize democratic norms like equal voice and accountability. The approach aligns well with existing strengths in low-resource and community-based ML.
